B5Grids: Detailed Construction
The B5Grids scheme is based on novel RSA- and identity-based schemes with location-based zero-
knowledge proof, providing a secure and efficient authentication scheme for offshore power grids.
The detailed construction of the proposed scheme is as follows.


Setup:
This algorithm runs primarily on the control center CC as follows.
– Let n = p · q be an RSA modulus
– Let e be a public exponent, d the private exponent (only known to the KGC)
– Let H1 : {0, 1}∗ → Z∗
n be a cryptographic hash function
– Generate RSA primes p, q, compute n = p · q, ϕ(n) = (p − 1)(q − 1)
– Choose e with gcd(e, ϕ(n)) = 1 and compute d = e−1 mod ϕ(n)
– Choose a generator g ∈ Z×
n
– Output M P K = (n, e, g), keep msk = d


KeyGen:
This algorithm runs on the control center CC and offshore entity as follows.
– Compute h = H1(ID)
– Set private key sk = hd mod n
– The corresponding public key is pk = gsk mod n; anyone can compute it from ID and M P K
– The CC securely sends sk to the turbine
Location proof π:
This algorithm runs on the turbine side with 6G-APS as follows.
– The 6G access points perform RTT and AoA measurements
– From these, an estimated position pos is computed
– A threshold k of APs collectively sign the statement “At time τ , device with temporary nonce
had position pos within error ε”
– The signed statement is π. The proof is verified by checking the signatures of the APs and
ensuring that the region defined by (pos, ε) is a subset of the authorized area L
Location-Based Authentication Scheme for 6G Cell-Free Offshore Power Grids 


Signing:
Given message m, private key sk, location proof π, current timestamp ts, and a random nonce r;
then this algorithm runs on the CC and GE as follows.
1. Compute c = H1(m ∥ π ∥ ts ∥ r)
2. Compute signature σ = (sk)c mod n
3. Output (σ, π, ts, r, ID)
Note: The random nonce r is provided by the network to prevent replay attacks.


Verification:
Given (σ, π, ts, r, ID) and message m; then this algorithm runs on the CC and GE as follows.
1. Check that ts is within an allowed window (±5 seconds)
2. Compute h = H1(ID) from the authorized list
3. Compute c = H1(m ∥ π ∥ ts ∥ r)
4. Verify that σe ≡ hc (mod n)
5. Verify π against the authorized area L for that ID
6. Accept if holds. Otherwise, abort
